[1]Gauzelin (died 962) was a French bishop of Toul.He was from a noble Frankish family, and made his way at court as a notary in the royal chancery.
[2]The king Charles the Simple made him bishop of Toul, and he was consecrated on 17 March 922.
[3]After the damage caused by Danish and Hungarian invasions, Gauzelin was a reforming bishop in his diocese, and founder of a number of monasteries.
Diagonal:2, Size:2
[7]He is a Catholic saint.
[6]Nancy Cathedral preserves a number of objects associated with him.
